  "text": "2 Two other models have given similar results. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] In addition, clinical studies have indicated that the signs and symptoms of local neuropathy in patients with lower extremity critical limb ischemia improve with intramuscular injection of VEGF gene. [CITATION_3] These findings implicate microvascular ischemia as an important and possibly principal cause of diabetic polyneuropathy, and suggest that angiogenic growth factors are a potential treatment.",
